  <h1>India vs England Test Series 2025</h1>
  <p>Thrilling Battle at Edgbaston</p>
</header>

<div class="container">
  <h2>Series Overview</h2>
  <p>The India vs England five-match Test series is currently underway. The second Test at Edgbaston, Birmingham has already produced history and high drama.</p>

  <h2>Historic Win at Edgbaston</h2>
  <p>India registered their <strong>first-ever Test win at Edgbaston</strong>, breaking a 58-year drought at the venue with a massive 336-run victory.</p>

  <h2>Batting Heroics</h2>
  <p><strong>Shubman Gill</strong> led from the front with scores of 269 and 161, totaling 430 runs in the match. Yashasvi Jaiswal and the middle order provided solid support.</p>

  <h2>Bowling Brilliance</h2>
  <p><strong>Akash Deep</strong> claimed 10 wickets in the match, including 6/41 in the second innings. <strong>Mohammed Siraj</strong> also shone with 6 wickets in the first innings.</p>

  <h2>England’s Struggles</h2>
  <p>England’s batting collapsed in both innings. Ben Stokes scored only 33 runs, and coach Brendon McCullum admitted to a poor toss decision.</p>

  <h2>Post-match Reactions</h2>
  <p><em>McCullum:</em> “We got the toss wrong and were second-best throughout.”<br>
     <em>Gill:</em> “The bowlers bowled with heart, and Akash Deep was magnificent.”</p>

  <h2>What’s Next?</h2>
  <p>The 3rd Test begins on July 10 at Lord’s, London. The series is level at 1–1.</p>

  <h2>Why This Win Matters</h2>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Key Stat</th><th>Detail</th></tr>
    <tr><td>First Edgbaston Win</td><td>India won here for the first time in Test history</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Biggest Overseas Win</td><td>Margin of 336 runs among India’s largest abroad</td></tr>
    <tr><td>New Star</td><td>Akash Deep’s debut brilliance</td></tr>
  </table>

